<strong><a class="contextual" name="1"></a>Collection and Use of Information</strong>

"Personally Identifiable Information" means specific information about users obtained via this Site that can be used to identify and contact a person, such as a person's name, a person's postal delivery address, a person's e-mail address, a person's payment method (e.g., credit card or debit card) and a person's telephone number.

When you register or re-register at this Site, we may ask you to supply us with Personally Identifiable Information and other information so that we can provide, enhance and personalize our services and marketing efforts. For similar reasons, we may supplement the Personally Identifiable Information you provide with publicly available information about you. We use this information to process your registration, your orders and your payments, and to communicate with you on these and other topics. We also use your e-mail address to send you newsletters, as well as messages about Meeting Tomorrow special offers, promotional announcements and consumer surveys. Occasionally, we may send these materials to you via postal mail, using the shipping address provided. Our packages that contain the rental equipment shipped to you may also contain promotional items or advertisements. If you no longer want to receive the newsletters, other announcements or non-equipment-package postal mail, simply send a quick e-mail to info@meetingtomorrow.com with the subject line, "Unsubscribe." Please note that you cannot unsubscribe from certain correspondence from us, including messages relating to your account transactions.

We track your interactions with us, including but not limited to your Site activity, rental selections, payment history and correspondence, as well as any incoming e-mails and related activity. We use this information for such purposes as personalizing the Site to better reflect particular interests, tracking your orders, and helping us quickly and efficiently respond to inquiries and requests and otherwise enhancing our service offering for our customers. We may also disclose and otherwise use, on an anonymous basis, certain information, such as, aggregate information, survey responses, consumption habits, commentary and non-personal information about users.

While using the Meeting Tomorrow service and Web site, you may have opportunities to post reviews or other personal information in public forums. Please understand that when you post such information, it is made public and is not subject to this policy.

