<strong><a class="contextual" name="6"></a>Disclosure of Personal Information</strong>

In an effort to serve you better, improve your online experiences and protect ourselves and others, we may share Personally Identifiable Information, in a reasonable manner as described below. In our sole discretion, we may sell, share or disclose any information about you that is not considered to be Personally Identifiable Information.

Except as otherwise provided, we will not sell your Personally Identifiable Information to third parties without notifying you of our intent to sell this information in advance and giving you a reasonable opportunity to prevent your Personally Identifiable Information from being sold.

Occasionally we use other companies, agents or contractors to perform services on our behalf. For example, we have partnered with other suppliers for various equipment and services. We also provide postal addresses to the U.S. Post Office or Federal Express delivery purposes. In the course of providing such services, these other companies may have access to Personally Identifiable Information.

We may release Personally Identifiable Information to third parties (i) to protect against or investigate fraud or other potentially harmful or illegal activities; (ii) if we reasonably believe disclosure is required by law; (iii) if we reasonably believe disclosure is necessary to establish or exercise legal rights; or (iv) to defend against claims or in situations involving potential threats to physical safety.

In the event that Meeting Tomorrow is acquired by or merged with a third party, we reserve the right, to disclose, sell or otherwise transfer all Personally Identifiable Information we have collected as part of or in connection with that transaction.

Other than as described above, with your consent, we may also share Personally Identifiable Information about you with third parties. Once we share Personally Identifiable Information with your consent to a third party, the use and protection of that information by the third party will no longer be subject to this Privacy Policy.

