<strong><a class="contextual" name="7"></a>Security</strong>

Meeting Tomorrow takes information security very seriously and uses reasonable administrative, technical and managerial measures to protect Personally Identifiable Information from unauthorized access. For example, we utilize Secure Sockets Layering, an industry-standard protocol for certain types of transmissions, in order to encrypt Personally Identifiable Information provided by you through the Site's registration and sign up process. Additionally, we store e-mail addresses and information regarding payment methods in an encrypted form. You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account information and for restricting access to your computer or mobile device through which you access this Site. Users of public or shared computers or unprotected mobile devices should log out at the completion of each visit to this Site.

By using this Site, you expressly agree that we can communicate with you electronically regarding Personally Identifiable Information, security, privacy, and administrative issues relating to information you have provided and/or your use of this Site.

Unfortunately, no security system can be guaranteed to be 100% secure. Accordingly, we cannot guarantee the information you provide to us and cannot assume liability for improper access to such information. By using this Site you agree to assume any security risks associated with that use.

